                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="1r" to="84va">1r-84va</locus>
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre. The ligature ግ+ዚ in እግዚአብሔር and እግዚእ
                           is used, but very inconsistently (cp. <locus target="#27v">27v</locus>,
                           47v).</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black and red (deep reddish brown [<locus target="#55r">55r</locus>], vivid vermilion [<locus target="#35rb">35rb</locus>,
                           41rb, etc.]).</seg>
                        Gabra Māryām is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#84va">84va</locus>.<date/>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ም or ምዕ for ምዕራፍ፡, በእ</abbr> for <expan>በእንተ፡ </expan> (<locus target="#84r">84r</locus>, 84v).</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; a few lines (some in groups of two)
                           alternating with black lines on the incipit page; numbers and headings of
                           the chapters; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the numerals
                           and of the quire marks.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="84va" to="85rb">84va-85rb</locus>
                     </handNote>
